<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1308,2025]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1308,1333]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species differs from the other species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[909,1060,1308,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Leucophenga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[909,1060,1308,1332]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Leucophenga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the epandrium entirely lacking seta (
<figureCitation box="[310,421,1344,1369]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1533,1555]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,302,1512]" captionTargetId="figure-187@42.[150,1436,301,1512]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 25. Leucophenga brevipenis Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia in lateral view. A. Epandrium, surstylus, and cercus; B. Hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, and aedeagus; C. Paramere; D. Aedeagus. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297938/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 25A</figureCitation>
); aedeagus subdorsolaterally with two long, subparallel processes; the thicker process bearing a sensillum at tip (
<figureCitation box="[448,552,1380,1405]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1533,1555]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,302,1512]" captionTargetId="figure-187@42.[150,1436,301,1512]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 25. Leucophenga brevipenis Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia in lateral view. A. Epandrium, surstylus, and cercus; B. Hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, and aedeagus; C. Paramere; D. Aedeagus. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297938/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 25D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1308,2025]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1416,1441]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Description.</emphasis>
Ocellar triangle dark brown, with ca. 2 setae above ocellar setae. Postocellar setae minute (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-89@19.[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga varinervis; D, E, F. L. acantha Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. alafumosa Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. brevipenis Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. brevitabulata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297906/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 6J</figureCitation>
). Frons brownish (
<figureCitation box="[409,496,1452,1477]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-89@19.[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga varinervis; D, E, F. L. acantha Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. alafumosa Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. brevipenis Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. brevitabulata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297906/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 6J</figureCitation>
). Orb 
<subScript attach="left" box="[566,574,1467,1481]" fontSize="6" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">3</subScript>
and Orb 
<subScript attach="left" box="[685,693,1467,1481]" fontSize="6" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">2</subScript>
parallel (
<figureCitation box="[813,900,1452,1477]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-89@19.[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga varinervis; D, E, F. L. acantha Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. alafumosa Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. brevipenis Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. brevitabulata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297906/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 6J</figureCitation>
). Pedicel brownish yellow to brownish; first flagellomere dark yellow (
<figureCitation box="[475,565,1491,1516]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-89@19.[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga varinervis; D, E, F. L. acantha Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. alafumosa Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. brevipenis Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. brevitabulata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297906/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 6J</figureCitation>
). Clypeus entirely brownish yellow. Palpus brownish yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1423,1491,1516]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-89@19.[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga varinervis; D, E, F. L. acantha Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. alafumosa Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. brevipenis Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. brevitabulata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297906/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 6J</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum mostly brownish yellow (
<figureCitation box="[580,670,1527,1552]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-89@19.[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga varinervis; D, E, F. L. acantha Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. alafumosa Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. brevipenis Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. brevitabulata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297906/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 6K</figureCitation>
). Postpronotal lobe dark yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1045,1133,1527,1552]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-89@19.[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga varinervis; D, E, F. L. acantha Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. alafumosa Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. brevipenis Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. brevitabulata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297906/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 6L</figureCitation>
). Acrostichal setulae in ca. 12–14 irregular rows (
<figureCitation box="[426,525,1563,1588]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-89@19.[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga varinervis; D, E, F. L. acantha Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. alafumosa Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. brevipenis Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. brevitabulata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297906/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 6K</figureCitation>
). Scutellum mostly brownish yellow (
<figureCitation box="[994,1092,1563,1588]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-89@19.[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga varinervis; D, E, F. L. acantha Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. alafumosa Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. brevipenis Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. brevitabulata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297906/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 6K</figureCitation>
). Pleura, katepisternum, and mesopleuron mostly dark yellow (
<figureCitation box="[532,619,1599,1624]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-89@19.[181,1406,193,1918]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga varinervis; D, E, F. L. acantha Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. alafumosa Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. brevipenis Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. brevitabulata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297906/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 6L</figureCitation>
). Wing (
<figureCitation box="[714,802,1599,1624]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1532,1554]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1511]" captionTargetId="figure-252@16.[151,1436,193,1511]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 3. Wing of male: A. Leucophenga alafumosa Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; B. L. brevipenis Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; C. L. brevitabulata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; D. L. delta Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; E. L. forcipula Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; F. L. fuscipalpula Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G. L. glabtabulata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; H. L. helvipecta Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297900/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
): entirely hyaline (
<figureCitation box="[1012,1099,1599,1624]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1532,1554]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1511]" captionTargetId="figure-252@16.[151,1436,193,1511]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 3. Wing of male: A. Leucophenga alafumosa Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; B. L. brevipenis Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; C. L. brevitabulata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; D. L. delta Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; E. L. forcipula Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; F. L. fuscipalpula Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G. L. glabtabulata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; H. L. helvipecta Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297900/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
); costal vein between R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1365,1389,1614,1628]" fontSize="6" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">2+3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[169,193,1653,1667]" fontSize="6" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">4+5</subScript>
distally with ca. 6 or 7 peg-like spinules on ventral surface; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[920,944,1653,1667]" fontSize="6" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">4+5</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1028,1036,1653,1667]" fontSize="6" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">1</subScript>
slightly convergent distally; halter yellowish, usually with brownish yellow patches at stem and knob (
