<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1625,1866]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1805,1830]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Etymology.</emphasis>
A combination of the Latin words: “ 
<taxonomicName box="[762,830,1805,1829]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis box="[762,830,1805,1829]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (= short) and “ 
<emphasis box="[1021,1080,1806,1829]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">penis</emphasis>
” (= aedeagus), referring to the short aedeagus.
</paragraph>
